I have a Python backtesting module that uses vectorized pandas operations for signal generation and portfolio construction. It currently runs a single backtest with fixed parameters. I want to extend it with walk-forward optimization: rolling train/test windows, parameter grid search on the train set, out-of-sample evaluation on the test set, and aggregate statistics across all windows. Turn this into an agent-ready spec. Here's the core structure:

```python
class Backtester:
    def __init__(self, data: pd.DataFrame, signal_func, portfolio_func):
        self.data = data
        self.signal_func = signal_func
        self.portfolio_func = portfolio_func

    def run(self, params: dict) -> BacktestResult:
        signals = self.signal_func(self.data, **params)
        positions = self.portfolio_func(signals)
        returns = positions.shift(1) * self.data['returns']
        return BacktestResult(returns=returns, positions=positions)
```
